/* ============================================================
 *  PIN / PERIPHERAL MAP  (edit here if you rewire)
 * ============================================================
 *
 *  POTENTIOMETER (RPM input)
 *  ─────────────────────────
 *  POT wiper  → PA1  (ADC1 Channel 1)
 *  POT VCC    → 3.3 V
 *  POT GND    → GND
 *
 *  TFT 1.8" ST7735 (SPI1, Software CS/DC/RST)
 *  ────────────────────────────────────────────
 *  TFT PIN    STM32 PIN   LABEL
 *  VCC        3.3 V
 *  GND        GND
 *  SCL        PA5         SPI1_SCK
 *  SDA        PA7         SPI1_MOSI
 *  CS         PA4         GPIO OUT (TFT_CS)
 *  DC/RS      PC4         GPIO OUT (TFT_DC)
 *  RES        PC5         GPIO OUT (TFT_RST)
 *  BL         3.3 V  (or PWM if brightness control needed)
 *
 *  CAN BUS (CAN1 via TJA1050)
 *  ────────────────────────────
 *  STM32 PD0  → CAN1_RX  → TJA1050 RXD
 *  STM32 PD1  → CAN1_TX  → TJA1050 TXD
 *  TJA1050 VCC → 5 V
 *  TJA1050 GND → GND
 *  TJA1050 CANH/CANL → CAN bus (120 Ω termination on each end)
 *
 *  BUZZER (Active buzzer, NPN-driven)
 *  ────────────────────────────────────
 *  PB0  → 1 kΩ → Base of NPN (e.g. 2N2222)
 *  Collector → Buzzer (+) → 5 V
 *  Emitter  → GND
 *  OR: PB0 directly to a 3.3 V active buzzer (check current!)
 *
 *  BOARD LED (LD4 on DISC1 = PD12)
 *  ─────────────────────────────────
 *  PD12  (built-in green LED — no extra wiring)
 *
 * ============================================================ */

